==English==
===Pronunciation===
*sô(r), /sɔː(r)/, /<tt>sO:(r)</tt>/
*:'''Homophones''': [[soar]]
*:[[Rhymes:English:-ɔː(r)|Rhymes: -ɔː(r)]]

===Noun===
'''sore''' (plural: ''sores'')

#An [[injured]], [[infected]], [[inflamed]] or [[diseased]] patch of [[skin]].
#:''They put ointment and a bandage on the '''sore'''.''

====Translations====
*Spanish: [[llaga]] {{f}}

===Adjective===
'''sore'''

#Causing [[pain]] or [[distress]]; [[painful]]ly [[sensitive]].
#:''Her feet were '''sore''' from walking so far.''
#Feeling mild animosity towards; [[annoyed]] or [[angered]].
#:''Joe was '''sore''' at Bob for beating him at checkers.''

====Translations====
*German: [[wund]] (1), [[sauer]] (2)
*Irish: [[tinn]] (1)
*Old English: [[wund]] (1)

